column5: Corey and I hit the islands area on Sunday to try for some pike.  The weather was beautiful, slight overcast and no wind (5 degrees).  Threw a bunch of baits but no takers.  The day wasn't an entire loss though, ran into some nice wildlife.  First was this guy....      Further along the shore, we ran into a few of these guys...       Lastly, we ran into this little guy.  I've been told it's a wood duck, is this correct ? I'm not sure what he was but he was sure nice looking.   I really like this shot...I caught him just as he was diving for some fish...   Even when you don't get any fish, it's still nice to get out.  Jim
Good Stuff Jim...  Great Pics, I'm sure the Boys Enjoyed it
Nice pics! Always good to get out and about and I'm sure Corey had a good time. Quality time with your son is always a good thing! Thanks for sharing.  Whopper
Who'd expext to see pictures of turtles swimming around Ontario waters in mid-January ??  Great stuff Jim and good to see you & Corey enjoying this weather
Sure looked like a nice day to get out there with nature (I'm stuck at home with a cold that just won't quit  ).  I love the last picture.  Joey
Seeing turtle in January is definitely worth your trip already  and the diving bird pic is really nice as well  Thank for the wonderful wildlife photos
Nice pic's Jimmy.  Can't wait to get out on Cooks with ya again for some Pike action.  Too bad the boats in dry dock!
Thanks for the replies folks !   Glad you joined the site Darren, great bunch of folks here  , you'll enjoy.
nice  the colds coming 14 day forecast says it's supposed to be frigid next week

very nice pics, especially the duck diving,  im no expert on ducks but know a little and it doesn't really look like a wood duck to me, if it is it's a female with very odd colour patches, at first look i would have said maybe a gadwall???????
Duck looks like maybe an Oldsquaw?? Can't believe the turtles aren't hibernating!
Wow, a Red Eared Slider! Those Turtles are native to the southern USA, I wonder how he got there?  Nice pics Misty.
Nice pics........the duck is a hen Oldsquaw......or long tailed duck.  Sinker
At least you got out, looks like a beautiful day...  Mike
